04/08/2010
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal (ICTY) prosecution has asked for a 27-year jail term for Croatian retired General Ante Gotovina, the court announced on Tuesday (August 3rd). The prosecution also recommends that the court sentence the other two defendants -- Mladen Markac and Ivan Cermak -- to 23 and 17 years in prison respectively. The three are charged with crimes against humanity and war crimes stemming from the 1995 Operation Storm. Their trial started in March 2008. (RTS, Beta, B92, AFP - 03/08/10)
